    <table border="0" width="85%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
      <table width=60% cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=center>

	<font color="#0e024d" face="Arial"><LEFT><big><strong>WIZARD KUNARK SPELL DETAILS - BETA LIST ONLY</strong></big><P>
<small><small>THIS SPELL LIST IS BETA ONLY - DETAILS <U>WILL</U> CHANGE REGULARLY UNTIL THE EXPANSION IS RELEASED, NOTHING IS CONFIRMED.</small></small></LEFT></font>
        <hr size="1" color="#0e042d">
	<tr><td valign='top' width='200'><font face='Arial'><small><b>Name: </font></small></b></td><td valign='top' width='400' colspan='2'><font face='Arial'><small>Sunstrike.</font></small></td></tr>
	<tr><td valign='top' width='200'><font face='Arial'><small><b>Level: </font></small></b></td><td valign='top' width='400' colspan='2'><font face='Arial'><small>60.</font></small></td></tr>
	<tr><td valign='top' width='200'><font face='Arial'><small><b>Mana: </font></small></b></td><td valign='top' width='400' colspan='2'><font face='Arial'><small>450.</font></small></td></tr>
	<tr><td valign='top' width='200'><font face='Arial'><small><b>Class: </font></small></b></td><td valign='top' width='400' colspan='2'><font face='Arial'><small>Evocation.</font></small></td></tr>
	<tr><td valign='top' width='200'><font face='Arial'><small><b>Vendor: </font></small></b></td><td valign='top' width='400' colspan='2'><font face='Arial'><small>Unknown.</font></small></td></tr>
	<tr><td valign='top' width='200'><font face='Arial'><small><b>Approx Spell Cost: </font></small></b></td><td valign='top'  width='400' colspan='2'><font face='Arial'><small>Unknown.</font></small></td></tr>
	<tr><td valign='top' width='200'><font face='Arial'><small><b>Researchable: </font></small></b></td><td valign='top' width='400' colspan='2'><font face='Arial'><small>No.</font></small></td></tr>
	<tr><td valign='top' width='200'><font face='Arial'><small><b>Type: </font></small></b></td><td valign='top'  width='400' colspan='2'><font face='Arial'><small>Fire Based Single Target Direct Damage Spell.</font></small></td></tr>
	<tr><td valign='top' width='200'><font face='Arial'><small><b>Actual Effects:</font></small></b></td><td colspan='2'><font face='Arial'><small>Target: Direct Damage (1615).</font></small></td></tr>
	<tr><td valign='top' width='200'><font face='Arial'><small><b>Description:</font></small></b></td><td valign='top' width='400' colspan='2'><font face='Arial'><small>Like the Ice Comet, this ball of flame from the Sun Itself is the most powerful fire based direct damage one hit spell in the game.  Providing a mana to damage ratio of well over 3.0 this spell will kill many mobs with one shot.
  <P>
On March 29 this spell had its mana cost changed from 475 to 450.<P>Casting Time: 7.0 Seconds<br>
Recast Time: Instant</font></small></td></tr>
	<tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td valign= 'top' colspan='2'><br><font face='Arial'><small>Click <b><a href='mailto:grimstaff@castersrealm.com?subject=You need to update info on Sunstrike - SpellID: 322'>Here</b></a> to report an error in this spells information.</small></font></td></tr>

	<tr>
	    <td>
		
		<TR>
		  <TD colspan=3><hr size='1'><font face='Arial' color='#0E024D'><b>Kudos to verant on this one</font></b><small><b><font face='arial'color='#0E024D'> -</font></small><font face='arial' color='#800000'><small> Menalaus</b></font></small></TD>
		</TR>

		<TR>
		  <TD colspan=3><font face='arial'><small>I had hoped for dammage exceeding 2 thousand, but 
1615 isn't too bad at all, especially since the 
cost mana wise is relative to ice comet (for 50 
more mana you are given at additional 495 points 
of dammage. Your reward for hitting level 60 is 
that extra dammage). Your potential dammage (based 
on level 50 mana) would be about ten thousand 
hitpoints of dammage as opposed to ice comet x6 
which is about 6700 points of dammage. I am not 
aware of how much mana a Wizard at level 60 
generates...and I don't want to even guess as it 
tends to lead to rumor. But wizards are now 
capable of at least 10k dammage with this spell. 
<P>
I would ask all newbies to refrain from commenting 
on this post, as those posts tend to be of ill-
informed nature without any high level experience. 
Keep in mind, that while 10K may be a lot of 
dammage, consider that as just a bruise to a God. 


		</small></font><BR></TD>
		</TR>
		
		<TR>
		  <TD colspan=3><hr size='1'><font face='Arial' color='#0E024D'><b>Bruise?</font></b><small><b><font face='arial'color='#0E024D'> -</font></small><font face='arial' color='#800000'><small> Koyasha</b></font></small></TD>
		</TR>

		<TR>
		  <TD colspan=3><font face='arial'><small>Actually, it has been speculated (though never 
proven, as far as I know) that max. HP in 
EverQuest is 32,000 HP.  The fact that NPC's seem 
to always strike themselves for this much when 
they commit suicide tends to lend weight to that 
theory - they're making sure they're dead, and 
thus striking for as many HP as they could 
possibly have.

Thus, 10,000 HP is no bruise, to anything..  It's 
about a third of a god's maximum hit points (as I 
understand it, both Lady Vox, Lord Nagafen, as 
well as Cazic Thule and Innoruuk have 32,000 HP - 
or so it has been approximately speculated).  Of 
course, I'd have to applaud the wizard that can 
manage to do this full damage potential to one of 
these beings and not be killed outright from it 
frenzying on her..

Note, of course, that the introduction of Kunark 
may easily have raised that 32,000 HP cap..  
Certainly, I'd say some NPC's need much higher HP 
levels (like the Gods, for example, and most 
likely the members of the Ring of Scale, whoever 
these ancient and powerful Wyrms are), several 
times that amount, infact..</small></font><BR></TD>
		</TR>
		
		<TR>
		  <TD colspan=3><hr size='1'><font face='Arial' color='#0E024D'><b>Spell Math</font></b><small><b><font face='arial'color='#0E024D'> -</font></small><font face='arial' color='#800000'><small> Rasema the High Elven Wizard of Fennin Ro</b></font></small></TD>
		</TR>

		<TR>
		  <TD colspan=3><font face='arial'><small>This spell is amazing.  I did the math, and, quite 
frankly, prepare to drool...

<br>At level 60 with 210 int, using the mana calc on 
this site, you will have 2640 mana.

<br>2640 divided by 450 is 5.866666.  That means you 
could cast this 1615 damage spell 5 times.

<br>Now, 450 times 5=2250, meaning the you are just 
450-(2640-2250) mana short of casting this spell 
again, which comes out to just 60.

<br>What with a casting time of 7 seconds and instant 
recast it would take you 35 seconds to cast this 
spell 5 times.

<br>Assuming that at level 60 you can recover 60 mana 
(a virtually invisible amount) in 35 seconds, that 
would mean you can cast this one more time without 
stopping.

<br>So, in the end, you would be able to cast 1615 
damage 6 times in 42 seconds(add 7 seconds to 35 
seconds for the sixth cast).

<br>Without resists the raw stats come out to. . .

<p>9690 damage
<br>42 seconds
<br>No mana left
<br>One freaking good spell

<p>Rasema the High Elven Wizard of Fennin Ro
(And addicted to EQ son of a math teacher)
		
		</small></font><BR></TD>
		</TR>
		
		<TR>
		  <TD colspan=3><hr size='1'><font face='Arial' color='#0E024D'><b>It doesn't stop there!</font></b><small><b><font face='arial'color='#0E024D'> -</font></small><font face='arial' color='#800000'><small> Evoker</b></font></small></TD>
		</TR>

		<TR>
		  <TD colspan=3><font face='arial'><small>Above we did the math with the numbers we DO 
control. I have heard that after 50 each point of 
INT is worth a lot more for mana. So the mana 
calculator is not the best answer...Lets say you 
have lots of mana...you can cast the spell 6 or 7 
times...but we forget specialization. The better 
you get at evocation the less mana you will use. 
So that means that with clarity on you will be 
able to basically banish Lady Vox with good 
taunters. Lets say a couple of tanks up front and 
a group of casters behind. If you risk taunting 
the God on you and get every spell off nicely with 
full damage you will do well over 12,000 points of 
damage in 1 minute if you recast instantly.

I think we wizards should praise Verrant and the 
EQ live team for this one. May the sun be with you</small></font><BR></TD>
		</TR>
		
		<TR>
		  <TD colspan=3><hr size='1'><font face='Arial' color='#0E024D'><b>Actually...</font></b><small><b><font face='arial'color='#0E024D'> -</font></small><font face='arial' color='#800000'><small> Shockwave</b></font></small></TD>
		</TR>

		<TR>
		  <TD colspan=3><font face='arial'><small>Actually you can cast the spell 6 time because of 
specialization.</small></font><BR></TD>
